nodes.text: Jeboe'i was a term used in the sport of phrenbi. Translating literally as "thieves", the jeboe'i were the neutral pair of teams to each pair of osk'y. While each pair of osk'y could only compete against each other, their jeboe'i could hinder their progress as there was only one b'rrsk in play at any team, and all four teams were competing for it.
